The paper deals with learning game representations from data, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of rationality constraints, which is a concept commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper formulates the learning problem as a constraint satisfaction problem, which is a topic in computer science (cs.DS).
